24-25 February - Greek Easter Bread

- 2 1/4 teaspoon dry yeast (1 package)
- 1     cup milk
- 1/4   cup lukewarm water
- 1     teaspoon salt
- 4     oz jar of cherries
- 1/4   cup margarine or butter
- 1     egg
- 3-4   cup flour
- hard boiled eggs
- sugar as directed in recipe


Combine yeast, water, 1 teaspoon sugar and let stand 5 minutes. Drain and chop cherries, set aside. Beat egg in large bowl. In a small pan, combine milk, salt, margarine, and 2 tablespoon sugar, still over low heat until warm, gradually stir into beaten egg and add 1 1/2 cup flour, add yeast, cherries and beat until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Knead 8-10 minutes. Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours. Knead again and shape. Let rise for 1 hour more. Make braids, snails, etc and insert your hard boiled eggs. Bake 350F for 40-45 minutes. 

Portuguese Sweet Bread

Use above recipe, increasing to: 
- 2   package of yeast (4 1/2 teaspoons) 
- 1/2 cup warm water 
- 1   cup sugar
- 3   beaten eggs
- 6-7 cup flour

To make small loaves, cook at 350F for 20 minutes.